                <note rend="inline" type="source">819.6156 T 61/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Panama</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">South</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-08-10T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 10, 1927—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. Legation’s telegram number 78, August 6, 2 p.m. As no reply to your note
                    regarding the Tonosí wireless concession appears to have been received, you
                    should see the President and ask him when a reply may be expected. You should
                    make it plain that the Department expects the reply will be favorable.</p>
                <p>When you have received assurances that the Government of Panama shares the views
                    of the Department as to the establishment of radio stations and the construction
                    of railroads in Panama you may inform the President orally that the Department
                    is not disposed to object to the contract between the Government of Panama and
                    the Chiriqui Land Company, but that the position of the Department with regard
                    to the question of radio and railroads remains as expressed to the Government of
                    Panama in former communications.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
